        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1946-06-11T18:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1946-06-11T18:00:00-05:00" n="1070" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1070">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">833.61311/6–1146</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in Uruguay</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Dawson</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">confidential</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1946-06-11T19:00:00-04:00">June 11, 1946—7 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>221. July wheat export program being finally determined. Pis cable whether <gloss target="#t_FonMin1">FonMin</gloss> considers report contained <gloss target="#t_urtel1">urtel</gloss> 325 June 8 changes <gloss target="#t_Urug1">Urug</gloss> need for US wheat to extent that July cargo can be
                        foregone.<note n="62" xml:id="d1070fn62">In telegram 333, June 13, 1946, 11
                        a.m., the Ambassador reported that no July cargo from the United States was
                        required (733.35/6–1346).</note> Urgent demand from famine areas makes US
                    export position extremely difficult.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Byrnes</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
